The Mapping editor consists of three main areas:

- **Mapping toolbar** with menu and action buttons

- **Mapping sidebar **with all scenes and pop-ups and their elements

- **Playback area** for previewing individual scenes and pop-ups

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Mapping toolbar
The Project toolbar provides general navigation, Project management buttons and quick access to key actions.

![](data:image/png;base64,)Mapping toolbar

- **Hamburger menu**

**Return to mappings:** Returns to the Mappings tab

- **Breadcrumb bar**

**Mapping:** Returns to the Mappings tab

- **Project name:** Open the Project editor of the associated Project

- **Schema name:** View and change the name of the Mapping

- **Copy icon:** Copy the UUID of the Mapping to the clipboard

- **Action buttons**

**Undo:** Undo the most recent change

- **Redo:** Restore changes that were previously undone

- **Save:** Save the Mapping in its current state

- **User information**

**Legacy Platform:** Switch to the legacy Babelee platform

- **Sign out:** Log out of the browser session

## Mapping sidebar
The sidebar contains a tab view of all scenes and pop-ups in the Project. Each tab contains a list of all elements in that particular scene or pop-up, which can be mapped to a data schema by clicking on the element.

Additionally, the **Advanced** tab contains extended settings which allow to control analytic tracking, Purl generation and dynamic storyboards.

![](data:image/png;base64,)Mapping sidebar with scene tabs and video elements

## Playback area
The large playback area allows to monitor any visual changes caused by mapping video elements to a data schema.

![](data:image/png;base64,)Playback area with a selected text element

> Tip: Edit data mappings during video playback

Use the playback area to identify and add missing data mappings. For example, you can click on a text element that appears during a scene. This opens the editing interface in the sidebar.

## User actions in the Mapping editor
The following actions can be performed from the Mapping editor:

- **Preview the scene or pop-up** in the playback area

- **Add dynamic data to an element**

- **Adjust the Mapping settings**
